The problem can be reproduced quite simple:
{quote}
<?php
$m = new MongoClient('mongodb://127.0.0.1');
$c = $m->selectCollection('test', 'test'); // non-existing collection
$i = $c->getIndexInfo();
$m->close();
var_dump($i);
{quote}
The code above results in Segmentation fault (var_dump is still fired).

All ok on existing collection:
{quote}
<?php
$m = new MongoClient('mongodb://127.0.0.1');
$c = $m->selectCollection('test', 'test');
$i = $c->insert(['test' => 'test']);
$i = $c->getIndexInfo();
$m->close();
var_dump($i);
{quote}

Newer versions of the server require that the [distinct|http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/reference/command/distinct/] command's {{query}} option be a BSON object, while previous versions allowed an array.

{noformat}
{
	"errmsg" : "exception: The query for the distinct command must be a document but was a Array",
	"code" : 18511,
	"ok" : 0
}
{noformat}

We should ensure that the PHP method's {{$query}} argument will serialize to an object by casting if necessary.

Pseudo-code:

class MySuperId extends \MongoId {
    public function __toString() {....}
}
bson_encode(['_id' => new MySuperId]);

Also, I would love to have ability to set non-default MongoId class for bson_decode().
Now I need to spend a lot of CPU for object convertation.

Real use case: base-62 (a-zA-Z0-9) encoding instead of base-16.

Thank you. Please fix it shortly, if you will.

